br>
<br>
I am new to this site, as far as posting, but have been reading it for while, and would ask some advice of you Warlords.<br>
<br>
I recently made a warrior (Tired of playing a cleric). He is a barbarian, and just made level 6. I had talked to a guildmate who played one and he suggested getting weapons with low delay, and low damage to work my melee skills up. The theory being, I would hit a lot, but for little damage, thus getting a lot of skill checks.<br>
<br>
So far havent seen many on weapons, but Offense skill is staying maxed. The problem is my Defense skill is only at 4, and I cant figure out why it isnt going up.<br>
<br>
I have a Iskar chestplate on him that gives regen, so I found a white mob, and just sat there and let him pound me for about 20 minutes, but never saw a increase.<br>
<br>
Am I doing something wrong? Or does it take a while for this to raise? Any suggestions or advice would be greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
Cairnwolf<br>
